              <h3 class="font-heading text-white text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Broadway & Downtown: Motor Burnout</h3>
              <p class="text-[#D4D4D4]">Nashville's Lower Broadway restaurants run exhaust systems 16-20 hours a day. Motors burn out faster in high-volume, grease-heavy environments. Direct-drive upblast fans with sealed motors last longer, but even they need replacement every 3-5 years under these conditions. If your motor is screaming, vibrating, or tripping breakers — <a href="/repair/nashville-tn/" class="text-[#FF5E15] hover:underline">call for emergency repair</a> before it seizes and takes the fan wheel with it.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
